@conservative_majority
title: It appears the Conservatives have a majority.
subtitle: Tories have enough seats ([+ conservative_majority +]%)
unavailable-subtitle: The DNVP is not interested in a coalition with the Center.
view-if: right_coalition >= 50
choose-if: year < 1929

The Tories have a majority in Parliament.

- @conservative_majority_sure: It appears the Tories win the election.

@no_conservative_majority
go-to: no_majority

This is very bad for us.

@liberal_majority
title: Liberal majority
subtitle: Liberal: [+ liberals_r +]%
view-if: liberals_r >= 50
on-arrival: Prime Minister = "Empty"; prime_minister_party = "Liberal"; liberals_in_government = 1; in_liberals_majority = 1; pro_republic += 5; foreign_minister_party = "Liberal"; foreign_minister = "Simon"; home_secretary_party = "Liberal"; home_secretary = "Samuel"; attorney_general_party = "Liberal"; attorney_general = "Hopkinson"; labour_minister_party = "Liberal"; labour_minister = "Harris"; secretary_of_state_for_war_party = "Liberal"; secretary_of_state_for_war_party = "Benn"; health_minister_party = "Liberal"; health_minister = "Addison"; chancellor_of_the_exchequer_party = "Liberal"; chancellor_of_the_exchequer_party = "Runciman"; agriculture_minister_party = "Liberal"; agriculture_minister = "Rew"; reichswehr_loyalty -= 0.05; 
achievement: majority_party

@conservative_majority_sure
subtitle: Theres no other path to government...
on-arrival: pro_republic -= 0; center_dissent += 0; left_dissent += 0; labor_dissent += 0; reformist_dissent += 0; neorevisionist_dissent += 0; elation -= 0; liberals_relation -= 0;


@no_majority
title: There is a hung Parliament.
view-if: labour_majority < 50
on-arrival: no_majority_elections += 1 Q.election_count += 1
go-to: no_majority_labour if prime_minister = "MacDonald" or prime_minister = "Asquith"; no_majority_tories if Q.election_count = 0 no_majority_liberals if liberals_seats > labour_seats
# TODO: if there is an anti-democratic coalition majority, you should appoint Papen.

@no_majority_labour
on-arrival: prime_minister = "MacDonald"; prime_minister_party = "Labour" labour_in_government = 1; in_labour_majority = 1; pro_republic += 5; foreign_minister_party = "Labour"; foreign_minister = "MacDonald"; home_secretary_party = "Labour"; home_secretary = "Henderson"; attorney_general_party = "Labour"; attorney_general = "Hastings"; labour_minister_party = "Labour"; labour_minister = "Shaw"; secretary_of_state_for_war_party = "Labour"; secretary_of_state_for_war_party = "Walsh"; health_minister_party = "Labour"; health_minister = "Wheatley"; chancellor_of_the_exchequer_party = "Labour"; chancellor_of_the_exchequer_party = "Snowden"; agriculture_minister_party = "Labour"; agriculture_minister = "Buxton"; reichswehr_loyalty -= 0.05;
